, \"to\": 218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A show-stopping performance by Celine Dion, a flaming Olympic cauldron lifted into the night sky by hot-air balloon, and a dazzling Eiffel Tower light show brought the curtain down on a four-hour celebration of French culture, history and art.\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.083526369537305e-29, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 432, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A show-stopping performance\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 248}, {\"ngram\": \"a flaming Olympic cauldron\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 291}, {\"ngram\": \"the night sky\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 317}, {\"ngram\": \"hot-air balloon\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 336}, {\"ngram\": \"a dazzling Eiffel Tower light show\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 376}, {\"ngram\": \"the curtain\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 396}, {\"ngram\": \"a four-hour celebration\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 428}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 455}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 463}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Braving torrential rain, some 300,000 people had lined the river banks to cheer on the armada carrying competitors past the city's iconic sights: the Eiffel Tower bearing the five Olympic rings, the Louvre and Notre Dame Cathedral.\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 665, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.6922278218008558, \"rank\": 0.44461110707505247, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"torrential rain\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 489}, {\"ngram\": \"some 300,000 people\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"the river banks\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"the armada carrying competitors\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 580}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's iconic sights\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 610}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 612, \"to\": 628}, {\"ngram\": \"the five Olympic rings\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wildly ambitious display was the first time the Olympic opening ceremony has been staged outside the main stadium, making it the biggest-ever launch for the \\\"Greatest Show on Earth\\\".\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 885, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wildly ambitious display\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 746}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic opening ceremony\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"the main stadium\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 816}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Greatest Show\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"Earth\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 883}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that gamble also made the ceremony hostage to the weather, with spectators, VIPs, and athletes alike drenched or huddling in transparent ponchos.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 1036, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that gamble\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 902}, {\"ngram\": \"the weather\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"VIPs\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"transparent ponchos\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some spectators refused to let the downpour get them down.\", \"from\